
[1]sparing

   SPA'RING, ppr.

   1. Using frugally; forbearing; omitting to punish or destroy.

   2. a. Scarce; little.

   3. Scanty; not plentiful; not abundant; as a sparing diet.

   4. Saving; parsimonious. Virgil being so very sparing of his words, and
   leaving so much to be imagined by the reader, can never be translated
   as he ought in amy modern tongue.
